WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.429 --> 00:00:02.562
<v ->Emmett Miller grew up as an outsider</v>

2
00:00:02.562 --> 00:00:04.514
in the harsh environment of New York.

3
00:00:04.514 --> 00:00:06.391
He was black, a Shakespeare fan,

4
00:00:06.391 --> 00:00:08.876
mathematics geek, and visionary.

5
00:00:08.876 --> 00:00:11.927
He didn't fit with the world of the black nor the whites.

6
00:00:11.927 --> 00:00:13.900
He witnessed firsthand how separatism

7
00:00:13.900 --> 00:00:16.215
was the prevailing political paradigm.

8
00:00:16.215 --> 00:00:17.932
Later in life as a medical student,

9
00:00:17.932 --> 00:00:20.470
he noticed that this same paradigm of separatism

10
00:00:20.470 --> 00:00:23.574
was being taught in relationship to patient care.

11
00:00:23.574 --> 00:00:25.835
This sent him on a lifelong quest

12
00:00:25.835 --> 00:00:28.459
to heal both patients and the planet.

13
00:00:28.459 --> 00:00:30.667
Emmett brings a loving heart and brilliant mind

14
00:00:30.667 --> 00:00:32.555
to the table of the paradigm shift,

15
00:00:32.555 --> 00:00:37.146
which he says cannot occur without deep self-examination.

16
00:00:46.378 --> 00:00:47.647
<v Regina>I love what you've done here,</v>

17
00:00:47.647 --> 00:00:50.069
but it's going to be quite a task

18
00:00:50.069 --> 00:00:52.383
for us to get through this in 45 minutes,

19
00:00:52.383 --> 00:00:54.431
because you want to heal the world.

20
00:00:54.431 --> 00:00:56.937
That's valiant and we need to heal the world,

21
00:00:56.937 --> 00:01:00.447
and we need people like you to do this, to guide us,

22
00:01:00.447 --> 00:01:02.622
but we're going to jump into --

23
00:01:02.622 --> 00:01:04.436
I want to get just a teeny bit of background

24
00:01:04.436 --> 00:01:06.739
on your motivation from medical school days,

25
00:01:06.739 --> 00:01:09.363
and seeing the huge disconnect in the way

26
00:01:09.363 --> 00:01:12.488
the system taught you to, quote, "heal people,"

27
00:01:12.488 --> 00:01:16.072
and society at large, and the globe.

28
00:01:16.072 --> 00:01:17.853
What was your initial experience

29
00:01:17.853 --> 00:01:21.122
that sent you down this road?

30
00:01:21.405 --> 00:01:24.660
<v ->Well, I think that soon after I arrived</v>

31
00:01:24.660 --> 00:01:29.535
in medical school and started working with patients,

32
00:01:29.535 --> 00:01:34.484
my clinical years, I was astounded to see

33
00:01:34.484 --> 00:01:38.963
what, basically, was a very abusive pattern

34
00:01:38.963 --> 00:01:42.728
between the medical system and the patient.

35
00:01:42.728 --> 00:01:45.331
Many physicians who were very fine men

36
00:01:45.331 --> 00:01:48.435
and who I continued to look up to and emulate,

37
00:01:48.435 --> 00:01:51.827
even to this day, who loved their patients,

38
00:01:51.827 --> 00:01:55.400
who felt for their patients, and who gave their patients

39
00:01:55.400 --> 00:01:58.791
more than just some drugs and surgery,

40
00:01:58.791 --> 00:02:03.303
but the system as a whole tended to select human beings

41
00:02:03.303 --> 00:02:07.762
to come into it that would participate in providing

42
00:02:07.762 --> 00:02:09.265
a decidedly un --

43
00:02:15.174 --> 00:02:19.547
an entirely inappropriate form of medicine,

44
00:02:19.547 --> 00:02:21.993
a real sub-standard form of medicine.

45
00:02:21.993 --> 00:02:23.795
<v Regina>Well, and they teach this in school even.</v>

46
00:02:23.795 --> 00:02:28.795
I was reading part of this culture on a couch concept here,

47
00:02:29.725 --> 00:02:32.041
and you were talking about, even in the system,

48
00:02:32.041 --> 00:02:34.388
when they teach you as an intern

49
00:02:34.388 --> 00:02:37.662
to not become emotionally involved with your patient.

50
00:02:37.662 --> 00:02:39.966
You can understand that in the extreme,

51
00:02:39.966 --> 00:02:42.536
but doesn't that toss out empathy?

52
00:02:42.536 --> 00:02:45.811
Doesn't it toss out a certain amount of compassion?

53
00:02:45.811 --> 00:02:47.581
What happens when the system is actually

54
00:02:47.581 --> 00:02:50.228
structured such a way?

55
00:02:50.228 --> 00:02:52.862
<v ->Well, what happens is we have a system which</v>

56
00:02:52.862 --> 00:02:56.819
is not aimed toward creating health, and wholeness,

57
00:02:56.819 --> 00:03:00.649
and healing, but is aimed at creating more business

58
00:03:00.649 --> 00:03:01.971
for the system.

59
00:03:01.971 --> 00:03:04.435
To not really provide people with what they need,

60
00:03:04.435 --> 00:03:07.123
and I'm not blaming any person.

61
00:03:07.123 --> 00:03:09.011
I'm simply talking about the system.

62
00:03:09.011 --> 00:03:12.978
We're all caught in a very dysfunctional system

63
00:03:12.978 --> 00:03:16.061
which is destroying us, and that became clear to me

64
00:03:16.061 --> 00:03:17.949
when I was in medical school.

65
00:03:17.949 --> 00:03:20.061
<v Regina>As you were looking at these people</v>

66
00:03:20.061 --> 00:03:22.919
with varying degrees of illness, you were also seeing

67
00:03:22.919 --> 00:03:24.071
the system that they had just

68
00:03:24.071 --> 00:03:26.044
plugged into to heal them as ill,

69
00:03:26.044 --> 00:03:28.412
and the system that's running that as ill.

70
00:03:28.412 --> 00:03:31.432
As you extrapolated out, you have a planet

71
00:03:31.432 --> 00:03:36.432
that is diseased, that is becoming very crippled.

72
00:03:36.659 --> 00:03:39.400
<v ->Yes, well growing up as a black man</v>

73
00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:42.418
in the '40s and the '50s, I experienced this

74
00:03:42.418 --> 00:03:45.618
incredible inequity of the system.

75
00:03:45.618 --> 00:03:50.618
At home, I lived in a neighborhood that was 98% black.

76
00:03:50.919 --> 00:03:53.959
When I was in school, because I was intelligent,

77
00:03:53.959 --> 00:03:57.671
I was surrounded by basically 100% white

78
00:03:57.671 --> 00:04:00.849
and Jewish people in New York City.

79
00:04:00.849 --> 00:04:05.222
Wonderful people, people had no sense, however,

80
00:04:05.222 --> 00:04:08.582
of what was being done to those of another color

81
00:04:08.582 --> 00:04:12.027
three blocks away from the school.

82
00:04:12.027 --> 00:04:16.848
There was such prejudice at that time.

83
00:04:16.848 --> 00:04:19.408
I had an opportunity to feel that prejudice.

84
00:04:19.408 --> 00:04:23.653
I had the opportunity to feel it at home, too, because

85
00:04:23.653 --> 00:04:26.234
because I was intelligent, because I read Shakespeare,

86
00:04:26.234 --> 00:04:29.295
because I was interested in math and physics,

87
00:04:29.295 --> 00:04:31.620
I was considered to be weird.

88
00:04:31.620 --> 00:04:35.748
At home, the black people considered me far too white

89
00:04:35.748 --> 00:04:37.679
to be fully included.

90
00:04:37.679 --> 00:04:40.719
White people considered me too black to be included,

91
00:04:40.719 --> 00:04:42.905
so I was never invited to any social functions

92
00:04:42.905 --> 00:04:46.158
or parties, all the usual things that happen

93
00:04:46.158 --> 00:04:48.547
in a racist society.

94
00:04:48.547 --> 00:04:52.377
I knew that this was part of the political system.

95
00:04:52.377 --> 00:04:54.670
Suddenly I found out that people were

96
00:04:54.670 --> 00:04:58.200
operating under the same principles

97
00:04:58.200 --> 00:05:01.293
in the medical system itself.

98
00:05:01.293 --> 00:05:03.565
People were not being attended to.

99
00:05:03.565 --> 00:05:05.304
They were being harmed.

100
00:05:05.304 --> 00:05:09.399
It became clear to me soon into my medical career

101
00:05:09.399 --> 00:05:12.621
that I could do more by touching a person,

102
00:05:12.621 --> 00:05:15.543
by touching them physically.

103
00:05:15.543 --> 00:05:19.170
Indeed, how I performed the physical examination.

104
00:05:19.170 --> 00:05:21.217
As I touched their body, I treated their body

105
00:05:21.217 --> 00:05:23.253
as though it was something precious,

106
00:05:23.253 --> 00:05:25.418
as though it was something beautiful.

107
00:05:25.418 --> 00:05:27.999
My goal was to discover, how could I lead

108
00:05:27.999 --> 00:05:32.340
this person to begin to make changes in their lives

109
00:05:32.340 --> 00:05:35.305
that would bring out the dormant beauty

110
00:05:35.305 --> 00:05:38.974
within that body that was called sick?

111
00:05:38.974 --> 00:05:42.270
Instead of doing what American medicine did,

112
00:05:42.270 --> 00:05:46.590
allopathic medicine, which was to try to fight the sickness,

113
00:05:46.590 --> 00:05:51.432
I recognized that 90% of the illnesses that people had,

114
00:05:51.432 --> 00:05:54.056
the physical illnesses that brought them to me

115
00:05:54.056 --> 00:05:55.773
as a physician, had their root,

116
00:05:55.773 --> 00:06:00.328
not in some external cause, but in an internal cause.

117
00:06:00.328 --> 00:06:02.024
It was the result of how they were dealing

118
00:06:02.024 --> 00:06:03.901
with stress in their lives.

119
00:06:03.901 --> 00:06:05.661
It had to do with the images that they

120
00:06:05.661 --> 00:06:07.527
were holding in their mind.

121
00:06:07.527 --> 00:06:09.330
Had to do with their self-image,

122
00:06:09.330 --> 00:06:11.378
how they saw themselves, how much value

123
00:06:11.378 --> 00:06:14.183
they placed in themselves, the amount of contact

124
00:06:14.183 --> 00:06:18.801
they had with a spiritual life, those things.

125
00:06:18.801 --> 00:06:21.478
The amount of contact they had with spiritual life,

126
00:06:21.478 --> 00:06:25.211
those are the things that ultimately would come out

127
00:06:25.211 --> 00:06:28.166
as physical symptomatology.

128
00:06:28.166 --> 00:06:31.920
I began to set my direction toward two things.

129
00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:35.077
First, deriving a system by which we could

130
00:06:35.077 --> 00:06:37.339
work with people, that would enable them

131
00:06:37.339 --> 00:06:40.080
to use their minds to awaken the intrinsic

132
00:06:40.080 --> 00:06:43.205
healing power that was obviously within people.

133
00:06:43.205 --> 00:06:45.137
I was able to demonstrate that over, and over,

134
00:06:45.137 --> 00:06:50.054
and over again in my clinical practice to my satisfaction.

135
00:06:50.054 --> 00:06:51.963
But, the question is, what can we do

136
00:06:51.963 --> 00:06:56.859
to maximize a person's ability to use the mind

137
00:06:56.859 --> 00:06:59.419
to awaken that healing power within,

138
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:01.872
and allow it to flow into those organs,

139
00:07:01.872 --> 00:07:03.941
and organ systems, and behaviors,

140
00:07:03.941 --> 00:07:08.941
and beliefs, and emotions where healing is needed.

141
00:07:09.306 --> 00:07:12.346
When that takes place, then the physical symptom

142
00:07:12.346 --> 00:07:14.618
resolves on its own.

143
00:07:14.618 --> 00:07:16.197
Not everything resolves.

144
00:07:16.197 --> 00:07:17.989
There are certain things that can't,

145
00:07:17.989 --> 00:07:21.615
but like 90% of what it is that bothers us

146
00:07:21.615 --> 00:07:23.674
can be resolved in that way.

147
00:07:23.674 --> 00:07:25.604
That became my work.

148
00:07:25.604 --> 00:07:26.980
That was number one.

149
00:07:26.980 --> 00:07:31.980
Number two was to change the medical system altogether.

150
00:07:32.313 --> 00:07:37.313
My belief is that in the changing how we look at healing,

151
00:07:37.561 --> 00:07:40.003
we change how we look at humanity,

152
00:07:40.003 --> 00:07:41.816
how we look at human beings.

153
00:07:41.816 --> 00:07:44.408
This would be a high leverage point

154
00:07:44.408 --> 00:07:46.456
for changing the paradigm with which

155
00:07:46.456 --> 00:07:49.571
the world looked at itself,

156
00:07:49.571 --> 00:07:53.464
with how people look at their relationships,

157
00:07:53.464 --> 00:07:55.352
their family, their community,

158
00:07:55.352 --> 00:07:58.061
people of other nations, or of other beliefs,

159
00:07:58.061 --> 00:07:59.415
or of other races.

160
00:07:59.415 --> 00:08:00.311
<v Regina>Absolutely.</v>

161
00:08:00.311 --> 00:08:02.658
I mean, healing extends out to all of those.

162
00:08:02.658 --> 00:08:03.724
<v ->Yes, yes.</v>

163
00:08:03.724 --> 00:08:07.185
The basic -- (sighs)

164
00:08:07.767 --> 00:08:09.345
One of the things I was looking for is,

165
00:08:09.345 --> 00:08:14.345
what is the most fundamental formulation of that,

166
00:08:14.924 --> 00:08:19.915
the formula for healing, as it were, the correction program.

167
00:08:19.915 --> 00:08:22.582
As a mathematician, because I was a mathematician

168
00:08:22.582 --> 00:08:24.438
before I went into medicine,

169
00:08:24.438 --> 00:08:26.763
and my specialty was point set topology,

170
00:08:26.763 --> 00:08:31.029
how you transform one space into another space.

171
00:08:31.029 --> 00:08:33.514
I simply used the principles of mathematics

172
00:08:33.514 --> 00:08:37.792
to look at illness as being a state.

173
00:08:37.792 --> 00:08:41.418
How can that state be transformed into another state

174
00:08:41.418 --> 00:08:44.577
that we can call health, or wellness --

175
00:08:44.577 --> 00:08:45.718
<v Regina>Or wholeness.</v>

176
00:08:45.718 --> 00:08:48.065
<v ->Or wholeness, or peak performance,</v>

177
00:08:48.065 --> 00:08:53.065
or joy, or love, or ecstasy.

178
00:08:53.888 --> 00:08:56.054
What would that be?

179
00:08:56.054 --> 00:09:00.085
That's what I worked on, is finding what is that,

180
00:09:00.085 --> 00:09:03.338
what is that fundamental healing formula?

181
00:09:03.338 --> 00:09:06.261
Realizing that when you find a fundamental formula

182
00:09:06.261 --> 00:09:08.129
within a system like that,

183
00:09:08.129 --> 00:09:10.273
it works at all levels of systems.

184
00:09:10.273 --> 00:09:12.844
Precisely the same formula will work

185
00:09:12.844 --> 00:09:15.307
for the individual healing within themselves,

186
00:09:15.307 --> 00:09:16.769
bringing mind, body, emotions, spirit,

187
00:09:16.769 --> 00:09:19.606
and behavior into balance.

188
00:09:19.606 --> 00:09:21.952
It works in a family or a community.

189
00:09:21.952 --> 00:09:23.947
It works at that level, or it can work

190
00:09:23.947 --> 00:09:27.104
at the level of a nation, or at the level of a planet.

191
00:09:27.104 --> 00:09:29.867
Precisely the same process.

192
00:09:29.867 --> 00:09:33.856
By refining that in the privacy and the intimacy

193
00:09:33.856 --> 00:09:37.461
of the one-to-one contact with thousands upon thousands

194
00:09:37.461 --> 00:09:41.962
of human beings, I was able to refine this

195
00:09:41.962 --> 00:09:44.543
to a certain degree.

196
00:09:44.543 --> 00:09:47.508
<v Regina>The world at large,</v>

197
00:09:47.508 --> 00:09:50.068
the world of medicine at large took

198
00:09:50.068 --> 00:09:52.667
a very different path than your path.

199
00:09:52.667 --> 00:09:53.765
<v ->Mm-hmm (affirmative).</v>

200
00:09:53.765 --> 00:09:55.210
<v Regina>All you have to do is</v>

201
00:09:55.210 --> 00:09:56.468
go into an HMO and this reason,

202
00:09:56.468 --> 00:09:58.953
say a Kaiser facility, and see the massive structures

203
00:09:58.953 --> 00:10:02.155
that are going up, the hallways crowded

204
00:10:02.155 --> 00:10:03.755
with people who are sick.

205
00:10:03.755 --> 00:10:08.755
It's amazing how ill we've become as a species, really.

206
00:10:10.229 --> 00:10:14.485
Yes, on one hand, you're looking at the quantum effect

207
00:10:14.485 --> 00:10:18.730
of healing the self, and you heal a portion or the whole.

208
00:10:18.730 --> 00:10:22.079
But let's take it to a non-quantum third dimensional view.

209
00:10:22.079 --> 00:10:26.206
How do we begin implementing this in the face of a system

210
00:10:26.206 --> 00:10:29.385
that has gone about its very narrow path

211
00:10:29.385 --> 00:10:31.635
that's every bit as deficient as it was

212
00:10:31.635 --> 00:10:35.795
when you were in medical school, if not worse now?

213
00:10:35.795 --> 00:10:40.094
<v ->Just as a human being brings healing to their lives,</v>

214
00:10:40.094 --> 00:10:43.155
whether it's physical, mental, emotional, relational,

215
00:10:43.155 --> 00:10:46.013
whatever it might be, behavioral,

216
00:10:46.013 --> 00:10:51.013
one brings healing into one's life by examining one's self,

217
00:10:51.560 --> 00:10:54.397
by being willing to step back,

218
00:10:54.397 --> 00:10:57.277
to step back from the usual decisions,

219
00:10:57.277 --> 00:11:01.084
to stop playing the game, "I'm right, and I know everything,

220
00:11:01.084 --> 00:11:04.359
"and that person's wrong, and that person's wrong."

221
00:11:04.359 --> 00:11:09.359
This defensive stance, what we call on the individual basis,

222
00:11:10.004 --> 00:11:13.396
the ego defenses.

223
00:11:13.396 --> 00:11:17.417
Because a person has been injured in their lives,

224
00:11:17.417 --> 00:11:22.259
in order to protect something very, very sensitive within,

225
00:11:22.259 --> 00:11:25.822
they construct a set of beliefs about the world,

226
00:11:25.822 --> 00:11:29.235
a set of ways of interpreting the world.

227
00:11:29.235 --> 00:11:33.683
"You're Christian, so you must be evil."

228
00:11:33.683 --> 00:11:35.709
Ways of interpreting the world

229
00:11:35.709 --> 00:11:40.709
and ways of behaving in the world.

230
00:11:41.705 --> 00:11:46.601
In order to resolve some of the inner conflicts

231
00:11:46.601 --> 00:11:48.414
with an individual, the inner conflicts

232
00:11:48.414 --> 00:11:52.713
that are making them ill, it becomes necessary

233
00:11:52.713 --> 00:11:56.307
to look at one's self and to look at this persona,

234
00:11:56.307 --> 00:11:59.027
to look at this ego that we've constructed,

235
00:11:59.027 --> 00:12:02.653
this PR agency that we've constructed

236
00:12:02.653 --> 00:12:06.066
to convince the rest of the world that we are

237
00:12:06.066 --> 00:12:09.522
whatever we're trying to convince them that we are,

238
00:12:09.522 --> 00:12:13.682
and to keep us convinced that we're okay.

239
00:12:13.682 --> 00:12:15.356
<v Regina>Right, that's the big one,</v>

240
00:12:15.356 --> 00:12:17.742
that self protection.

241
00:12:18.569 --> 00:12:20.649
This really requires an extreme amount

242
00:12:20.649 --> 00:12:24.179
of openness, vulnerability, and re-education.

243
00:12:24.179 --> 00:12:25.086
<v ->Yes.</v>

244
00:12:25.086 --> 00:12:26.430
<v Regina>I'm just going to pull one little fact</v>

245
00:12:26.430 --> 00:12:28.222
from your manuscript that I've read,

246
00:12:28.222 --> 00:12:30.707
just because it kind of hits it square on, which is

247
00:12:30.707 --> 00:12:33.427
our way of dealing with things.

248
00:12:33.427 --> 00:12:36.509
"In California, between the years of 1980 and 1998,"

249
00:12:36.509 --> 00:12:41.021
you say, "California built 21 prisons and one college

250
00:12:41.021 --> 00:12:43.101
"in the same time period."

251
00:12:43.101 --> 00:12:44.615
What does that say about the way

252
00:12:44.615 --> 00:12:47.356
we're going about healing this thing?

253
00:12:47.356 --> 00:12:50.044
Education certainly is not the priority here, is it?

254
00:12:50.044 --> 00:12:51.026
<v ->No.</v>

255
00:12:51.026 --> 00:12:53.372
Well, we're not aiming to heal it.

256
00:12:53.372 --> 00:12:55.783
That's not what our behavior is.

257
00:12:55.783 --> 00:12:57.457
Maybe it's what we really want.

258
00:12:57.457 --> 00:13:00.220
I believe it's what we really want,

259
00:13:00.220 --> 00:13:04.006
