00:25:34.752 --> 00:25:36.427
into smaller and smaller places,

518
00:25:36.427 --> 00:25:38.773
because there's a lot of money available

519
00:25:38.773 --> 00:25:40.469
to somebody who knows the technology

520
00:25:40.469 --> 00:25:42.976
of condensing power into the hands

521
00:25:42.976 --> 00:25:45.290
of a small number of people.

522
00:25:45.290 --> 00:25:50.290
The PR agencies, lobbyists, and so forth.

523
00:25:52.717 --> 00:25:54.968
That's what the system's doing out there,

524
00:25:54.968 --> 00:25:58.402
creating, not wholeness, but more separation,

525
00:25:58.402 --> 00:26:00.655
more dispersion, and more violence.

526
00:26:00.655 --> 00:26:03.044
Okay, so we come within to ourselves,

527
00:26:03.044 --> 00:26:07.022
reach that place of wisdom, look honestly at the world

528
00:26:07.022 --> 00:26:10.179
to see it as it truly is, so look honestly at myself,

529
00:26:10.179 --> 00:26:12.291
to realize the power that I have.

530
00:26:12.291 --> 00:26:15.491
As an American, to realize that I'm using

531
00:26:15.491 --> 00:26:19.885
three to four times more of the earth's bounty

532
00:26:19.885 --> 00:26:23.693
than people in poor countries.

533
00:26:23.693 --> 00:26:24.984
Is that okay?

534
00:26:24.984 --> 00:26:26.658
Is it okay?

535
00:26:26.658 --> 00:26:30.007
Where do I find that arrogance within me

536
00:26:30.007 --> 00:26:33.026
that allows me to go out and by a Porsche,

537
00:26:33.026 --> 00:26:37.228
while a baby starves to death every three minutes,

538
00:26:37.228 --> 00:26:39.320
or every three seconds?

539
00:26:39.320 --> 00:26:41.112
It's unbelievable.

540
00:26:41.112 --> 00:26:42.989
<v Regina>It seems that to sustain that kind of system,</v>

541
00:26:42.989 --> 00:26:44.941
you really do have to be more or less

542
00:26:44.941 --> 00:26:46.893
in isolation from each other too.

543
00:26:46.893 --> 00:26:49.165
What would happen if people started talking,

544
00:26:49.165 --> 00:26:51.192
and holding hands, and realizing,

545
00:26:51.192 --> 00:26:53.719
we're more alike than we are dissimilar.

546
00:26:53.719 --> 00:26:55.970
To keep people apart, as you say,

547
00:26:55.970 --> 00:26:58.967
the separatism is really critical to the system.

548
00:26:58.967 --> 00:27:01.634
You have been trying to work for a very long time

549
00:27:01.634 --> 00:27:04.471
at bringing people together, at getting dialogue

550
00:27:04.471 --> 00:27:07.414
across all boundaries going.

551
00:27:07.414 --> 00:27:09.622
Is this really a key element?

552
00:27:09.622 --> 00:27:12.918
<v ->Yes, it's a crucial element.</v>

553
00:27:12.918 --> 00:27:16.054
We've become accustomed to having someone else

554
00:27:16.054 --> 00:27:19.030
tell us what to do, to see our leadership

555
00:27:19.030 --> 00:27:20.950
as coming from outside.

556
00:27:20.950 --> 00:27:24.043
However we define it, as our father,

557
00:27:24.043 --> 00:27:26.453
or our scout leader, our teacher,

558
00:27:26.453 --> 00:27:31.453
or a super model, or our president,

559
00:27:32.076 --> 00:27:35.276
or our priest, or whoever it might be.

560
00:27:35.276 --> 00:27:37.915
We're accustomed to being led from outside.

561
00:27:37.915 --> 00:27:39.718
<v Regina>You mean the great unifier?</v>

562
00:27:39.718 --> 00:27:40.955
<v ->Yes. (laughing)</v>

563
00:27:40.955 --> 00:27:43.163
<v Regina>I love that one, our president.</v>

564
00:27:43.163 --> 00:27:44.134
<v ->Right.</v>

565
00:27:44.134 --> 00:27:45.691
<v Regina>Declaring he is the great unifier</v>

566
00:27:45.691 --> 00:27:49.008
at a time there's never been more division and strife.

567
00:27:49.008 --> 00:27:50.608
Quite interesting.

568
00:27:50.608 --> 00:27:51.845
I'm sorry, go ahead.

569
00:27:51.845 --> 00:27:53.285
Just had to put that one in there.

570
00:27:53.285 --> 00:27:54.256
<v ->Right.</v>

571
00:27:54.256 --> 00:27:56.026
He turned out to be the great decider instead,

572
00:27:56.026 --> 00:27:57.509
which he definitely was.

573
00:27:57.509 --> 00:28:00.507
<v Regina>Oh yeah, the great decider, the great divider.</v>

574
00:28:03.421 --> 00:28:08.060
<v ->Even if we look at the highest echelons of government,</v>

575
00:28:08.060 --> 00:28:12.775
we see that people are being led, not from their hearts,

576
00:28:12.775 --> 00:28:17.489
not from their wisdom, but from some catechism,

577
00:28:17.489 --> 00:28:20.742
some set of rules, some set of principles

578
00:28:20.742 --> 00:28:24.081
that they're following, or that their cabinet

579
00:28:24.081 --> 00:28:25.734
is telling them.

580
00:28:25.734 --> 00:28:27.568
<v Regina>Like an invisible hand.</v>

581
00:28:27.568 --> 00:28:30.374
<v ->It is an invisible hand, and it's maintained</v>

582
00:28:30.374 --> 00:28:35.374
by this denial, by our inability to really see who we are,

583
00:28:35.621 --> 00:28:38.757
and to really see who others are.

584
00:28:38.757 --> 00:28:42.032
Connecting with others is crucial.

585
00:28:42.032 --> 00:28:44.581
That's why we work with the World Cafe.

586
00:28:44.581 --> 00:28:45.765
<v Regina>Let's get into that.</v>

587
00:28:45.765 --> 00:28:49.015
Yes, please, tell us about the World Cafe.

588
00:28:50.441 --> 00:28:53.502
<v ->After I had defined for myself the principles</v>

589
00:28:53.502 --> 00:28:56.969
of mind-body medicine for use with individuals,

590
00:28:56.969 --> 00:29:00.072
I studied with a wonderful woman, Virginia Satir,

591
00:29:00.072 --> 00:29:01.822
and learned about how to apply

592
00:29:01.822 --> 00:29:04.808
those principles in families.

593
00:29:04.808 --> 00:29:08.669
Then, in the 1980s, I worked with Juanita Brown,

594
00:29:08.669 --> 00:29:10.664
and we looked at how to use these principles

595
00:29:10.664 --> 00:29:15.664
into organizations, how a company could be driven

596
00:29:15.794 --> 00:29:18.599
by their shared spirit, how there could be

597
00:29:18.599 --> 00:29:22.642
a collective sense of wholeness, of consciousness.

598
00:29:22.642 --> 00:29:24.103
How we could be deeply committed

599
00:29:24.103 --> 00:29:26.033
to the same thing and support ourselves,

600
00:29:26.033 --> 00:29:29.404
and create high-performance organizations.

601
00:29:30.504 --> 00:29:33.778
Dr. Brown continued in the 1990s to develop,

602
00:29:33.778 --> 00:29:37.810
using these same principles, the World Cafe.

603
00:29:37.810 --> 00:29:41.639
The World Cafe is sort of her recognition

604
00:29:41.639 --> 00:29:44.497
that some of the best and most important thinking

605
00:29:44.497 --> 00:29:47.932
goes on over a cup of tea or a cup of coffee.

606
00:29:47.932 --> 00:29:50.748
In the old style, for instance, in the European,

607
00:29:50.748 --> 00:29:52.763
it's at a cafe.

608
00:29:52.763 --> 00:29:56.475
In drawing a group of people together

609
00:29:56.475 --> 00:29:59.750
to think about something, whether it was a company,

610
00:29:59.750 --> 00:30:04.304
or an organization, or it might be two or three

611
00:30:04.304 --> 00:30:06.437
elements of a community that were having

612
00:30:06.437 --> 00:30:08.549
a disagreement about something.

613
00:30:08.549 --> 00:30:13.264
She would have them meet all around little tables

614
00:30:13.264 --> 00:30:15.589
of four to six people per table

615
00:30:15.589 --> 00:30:17.935
in a cafe kind of atmosphere.

616
00:30:17.935 --> 00:30:21.444
Nice music playing in the background, flowers on the table,

617
00:30:21.444 --> 00:30:25.295
paper tablecloth with colored pens at the table

618
00:30:25.295 --> 00:30:29.711
so that people could sketch and draw as they talk.

619
00:30:29.711 --> 00:30:32.516
You would have three people from, let's say,

620
00:30:32.516 --> 00:30:34.276
three people from one point of view

621
00:30:34.276 --> 00:30:36.857
meeting with three people from the other point of view

622
00:30:36.857 --> 00:30:39.833
around many, many different little tables.

623
00:30:39.833 --> 00:30:44.632
She would have them, initially, discuss something like,

624
00:30:44.632 --> 00:30:48.355
"What is it that has drawn you into

625
00:30:48.355 --> 00:30:52.130
"being interested in this topic that brings us together?"

626
00:30:52.130 --> 00:30:55.757
People would entertain that question together

627
00:30:55.757 --> 00:30:58.477
for maybe 15 minutes.

628
00:30:58.477 --> 00:31:02.370
Everybody would share their personal perspective.

629
00:31:02.370 --> 00:31:07.370
Then there would be a break, and all except one

630
00:31:08.044 --> 00:31:10.017
of the people would get up from that table

631
00:31:10.017 --> 00:31:13.635
and find a new table, and re-sort themselves.

632
00:31:13.635 --> 00:31:16.055
The person who remained was the host.

633
00:31:16.055 --> 00:31:19.191
As each new person came, introduced themselves,

634
00:31:19.191 --> 00:31:23.714
they'd sit down, and he would share or she would share

635
00:31:23.714 --> 00:31:25.292
what happened in their group.

636
00:31:25.292 --> 00:31:27.457
Each of the people arriving, "Well, that's interesting,

637
00:31:27.457 --> 00:31:30.081
"because we found in our group so-and-so."

638
00:31:30.081 --> 00:31:32.236
Then after a minute or two, she would say,

639
00:31:32.236 --> 00:31:34.465
"Okay, we're going to go to another question."

640
00:31:34.465 --> 00:31:35.980
She would ask, perhaps the same question,

641
00:31:35.980 --> 00:31:38.667
or maybe another question, such as,

642
00:31:38.667 --> 00:31:41.590
"If we were able to create peace and wholeness

643
00:31:41.590 --> 00:31:45.590
"in this community, what's your best dream

644
00:31:45.590 --> 00:31:49.301
"for how the outcome could look if we were successful?

645
00:31:49.301 --> 00:31:52.416
"Don't ask how, but suppose it all worked out."

646
00:31:52.416 --> 00:31:55.616
People would again share, but the idea in sharing

647
00:31:55.616 --> 00:31:59.082
is not to make other people listen to your point of view,

648
00:31:59.082 --> 00:32:01.695
but listen to the concept that's arising

649
00:32:01.695 --> 00:32:03.604
in the middle of the table,

650
00:32:03.604 --> 00:32:06.111
the magic in the middle, the unity.

651
00:32:06.111 --> 00:32:07.882
Where do we all connect?

652
00:32:07.882 --> 00:32:09.268
Don't worry about how we differ,

653
00:32:09.268 --> 00:32:10.964
focus on how we connect.

654
00:32:10.964 --> 00:32:14.281
After 15 minutes, they may break and go to another table,

655
00:32:14.281 --> 00:32:15.913
maybe answer another question.

656
00:32:15.913 --> 00:32:20.574
Well, the energy in the room starts going higher and higher

657
00:32:20.574 --> 00:32:22.974
as people start making personal contact,

658
00:32:22.974 --> 00:32:25.662
respecting other people's values,

659
00:32:25.662 --> 00:32:28.723
respecting the principles that they live by,

660
00:32:28.723 --> 00:32:31.560
respecting the vision and intelligence they have.

661
00:32:31.560 --> 00:32:35.037
All of the sudden, says, "Oh my gosh, you know,

662
00:32:35.037 --> 00:32:37.458
"he's an immigrant but he's intelligent,

663
00:32:37.458 --> 00:32:39.965
"and he loves his family just as I do."

664
00:32:39.965 --> 00:32:41.170
<v Regina>He wants the same things</v>

665
00:32:41.170 --> 00:32:43.378
for his family, and his community, and his world.

666
00:32:43.378 --> 00:32:44.743
<v ->Yeah, exactly.</v>

667
00:32:44.743 --> 00:32:47.346
"Well, gee, if it's possible for us to solve this

668
00:32:47.346 --> 00:32:50.300
"in a way that satisfies everybody's needs,

669
00:32:50.300 --> 00:32:52.850
"boy, I really want to do that."

670
00:32:52.850 --> 00:32:55.473
Then we'd stop the cafe for a moment

671
00:32:55.473 --> 00:32:56.913
and people would share out,

672
00:32:56.913 --> 00:33:00.049
"What do you hear emerging from the conversations

673
00:33:00.049 --> 00:33:01.979
"that you've been in?"

674
00:33:01.979 --> 00:33:04.721
People stand up, and these wonderfully

675
00:33:04.721 --> 00:33:07.057
creative ideas come about.

676
00:33:07.057 --> 00:33:09.456
Meanwhile, we have a graphic recorder

677
00:33:09.456 --> 00:33:12.560
who's recording all these things that are being spoken

678
00:33:12.560 --> 00:33:16.837
by drawing beautiful pictures, visual graphics,

679
00:33:16.837 --> 00:33:20.229
as well as a few words, so at the end of the day,

680
00:33:20.229 --> 00:33:21.829
and there are a few other things that we do,

681
00:33:21.829 --> 00:33:23.290
but you get the idea.

682
00:33:23.290 --> 00:33:25.839
It's how you develop that wholeness,

683
00:33:25.839 --> 00:33:27.791
represented graphically in such a way

684
00:33:27.791 --> 00:33:29.999
that people can, later in the day,

685
00:33:29.999 --> 00:33:31.855
simply look through the images there

686
00:33:31.855 --> 00:33:35.204
and remember the whole path of the conversation

687
00:33:35.204 --> 00:33:36.804
of this group of people.

688
00:33:36.804 --> 00:33:41.102
That may be 12 people, or it could be 1200,

689
00:33:41.102 --> 00:33:43.908
or I think it's been up to 6 or 7,000 people

690
00:33:43.908 --> 00:33:46.179
have been worked with in this way.

691
00:33:46.179 --> 00:33:49.150
<v Regina>This is a global affair.</v>

692
00:33:49.150 --> 00:33:50.744
<v ->That's right.</v>

693
00:33:51.422 --> 00:33:54.142
We've made a couple of videos of it

694
00:33:54.142 --> 00:33:57.160
that are available right now at places like,

695
00:33:57.160 --> 00:33:59.976
on TheWorldCafe.com.

696
00:33:59.976 --> 00:34:03.432
You can see videos of just how it works

697
00:34:03.432 --> 00:34:05.778
and what people's experience of it is.

698
00:34:05.778 --> 00:34:07.826
It doesn't belong to anybody.

699
00:34:07.826 --> 00:34:10.354
This isn't a company.

700
00:34:10.354 --> 00:34:14.140
Juanita and her partner did a wonderful thing

701
00:34:14.140 --> 00:34:18.023
after building this for years, just last year,

702
00:34:18.023 --> 00:34:21.404
they gave it to the World Cafe community.

703
00:34:21.404 --> 00:34:25.052
It's about 5 or 10,000 people who are practicing it.

704
00:34:25.052 --> 00:34:29.094
It brings community and harmony to groups of people,

705
00:34:29.094 --> 00:34:33.808
and most important, teaches them the value,

706
00:34:33.808 --> 00:34:35.707
and the importance, and the technology

707
00:34:35.707 --> 00:34:39.632
of how to have good conversations with another person,

708
00:34:39.632 --> 00:34:41.957
how to have a conversation with a person

709
00:34:41.957 --> 00:34:44.389
where you respect the other person,

710
00:34:44.389 --> 00:34:47.013
where you honestly appreciate that person,

711
00:34:47.013 --> 00:34:51.130
where you honor and appreciate that person's beliefs

712
00:34:51.130 --> 00:34:53.519
and their standards, where you trust

713
00:34:53.519 --> 00:34:57.146
that there's another loving human being inside the other,

714
00:34:57.146 --> 00:35:00.294
even if it's an adversary.

715
00:35:00.294 --> 00:35:04.080
To use Gandhi's admonition, which is,

716
00:35:04.080 --> 00:35:06.267
"The ally you must always seek

717
00:35:06.267 --> 00:35:10.277
"is the part of your adversary that knows what is right."

718
00:35:10.277 --> 00:35:13.018
That's what's going to save the world,

719
00:35:13.018 --> 00:35:14.831
because you know what we need,

720
00:35:14.831 --> 00:35:17.477
and I know what we need.

721
00:35:17.477 --> 00:35:19.642
Mr. Bush knows what we need.

722
00:35:19.642 --> 00:35:22.916
Osama Bin Laden knows what we need.

723
00:35:22.916 --> 00:35:25.007
The man next door knows what we need.

724
00:35:25.007 --> 00:35:28.580
The people down where you work know what we need.

725
00:35:28.580 --> 00:35:33.580
All we need to do is to learn how to be quiet for a while,

726
00:35:34.223 --> 00:35:37.211
to look within, and to realize that we need to

727
00:35:37.211 --> 00:35:40.251
awaken the leader that's inside,

728
00:35:40.251 --> 00:35:42.672
that we need to lead our own lives.

729
00:35:42.672 --> 00:35:46.032
I talked before about this pyramidal structure

730
00:35:46.032 --> 00:35:49.306
that most of the organizations,

731
00:35:49.306 --> 00:35:53.231
and gatherings, and communities in our culture have,

732
00:35:53.231 --> 00:35:56.228
in which there's the top guy, who's really powerful,

733
00:35:56.228 --> 00:36:01.177
and a few people that will take a bullet for the top guy,

734
00:36:01.177 --> 00:36:03.375
and so forth down like that.

735
00:36:03.375 --> 00:36:05.007
Instead of looking for that leadership

736
00:36:05.007 --> 00:36:08.004
just coming from the outside, because we've been misled,

737
00:36:08.004 --> 00:36:12.025
enormously, enormously misled.

738
00:36:12.025 --> 00:36:15.854
When you talk about conflict, when you talk about

739
00:36:15.854 --> 00:36:18.712
the division between people, when you talk about

740
00:36:18.712 --> 00:36:21.006
what I saw in medicine or what you see in the building

741
00:36:21.006 --> 00:36:24.451
of jails instead of hospitals, think about people

742
00:36:24.451 --> 00:36:28.738
being murdered in wars, and being sent home

743
00:36:28.738 --> 00:36:30.690
without arms and legs.

744
00:36:30.690 --> 00:36:32.697
We just look at, "Oh, it's only 4 or 5,000

745
00:36:32.697 --> 00:36:34.851
"that have been killed in the war."

746
00:36:34.851 --> 00:36:37.593
Five times that many have physical illnesses

747
00:36:37.593 --> 00:36:41.006
that are going to plague them for the rest of their lives --

748
00:36:41.006 --> 00:36:42.542
<v Regina>That doesn't even count the Iraqis,</v>

749
00:36:42.542 --> 00:36:43.672
quote, "the enemy."

750
00:36:43.672 --> 00:36:45.112
<v ->Right, thank you.</v>

751
00:36:45.112 --> 00:36:46.808
<v Regina>Goodness, children and women.</v>

752
00:36:46.808 --> 00:36:47.789
<v ->Absolutely.</v>

753
00:36:47.789 --> 00:36:51.149
The estimate is 80 to a million have been killed,

754
00:36:51.149 --> 00:36:52.685
and how many have been wounded?

755
00:36:52.685 --> 00:36:56.471
Let's not even talk about the psychological damage

756
00:36:56.471 --> 00:36:57.655
that's been done.

757
00:36:57.655 --> 00:37:01.484
That's not talk about the enemies that we're all making.

758
00:37:01.484 --> 00:37:04.503
Insane, and war after war.

759
00:37:04.503 --> 00:37:08.919
We start the Spanish American War, and blame it on Spain

760
00:37:08.919 --> 00:37:12.844
because we want Cuba, and we die for that.

761
00:37:12.844 --> 00:37:16.460
The Gulf of Tonkin event, purely fictitious.

762
00:37:16.460 --> 00:37:17.686
There was no shooting.

763
00:37:17.686 --> 00:37:19.225
I know a man who was on the boat.

764
00:37:19.225 --> 00:37:20.761
There was no shooting.

765
00:37:20.761 --> 00:37:25.020
Everyone who died in Vietnam, all of that

766
00:37:25.020 --> 00:37:28.945
agony that went on in our culture,

767
00:37:28.945 --> 00:37:30.502
parents disowning their children

768
00:37:30.502 --> 00:37:32.379
for burning their draft cards,

769
00:37:32.379 --> 00:37:34.662
the shootings at Kent State.

770
00:37:34.662 --> 00:37:38.533
60,000 died in the war, more than twice that many

771
00:37:38.533 --> 00:37:41.275
have committed suicide since they've come home

772
00:37:41.275 --> 00:37:43.248
because of a lie.

773
